items.abstract: <jats:p>From the leaves of <jats:italic>Grossheimia macrocephala</jats:italic> (MUSS.-PUSCHK.) D. SOSN. et TAKHT. cynaropicrin (<jats:italic>II</jats:italic>), isolipidiol (<jats:italic>III</jats:italic>) and the so far undescribed lactone grosheiminol (<jats:italic>IV</jats:italic>) were isolated in addition to grosheimin (<jats:italic>I</jats:italic>), detected in this species earlier. For grosheiminol the structure <jats:italic>IV</jats:italic> was derived, including relative and absolute configuration, on the basis of chemical correlation.</jats:p>
